{"actor":{"login":"edithatogo","type":"github-user"},"artifacts":[],"command":null,"entry_sha256":"8c969f7991406c0f973d43115f17f9a3da4b17e58e0ad1b8229cb96f9dc49a3e","event_id":"00000000-0000-4000-8000-000000000009","gate_ref":null,"kind":"review","phase":"retrospective","previous_entry_sha256":null,"recorded_at":"2026-07-19T03:10:33Z","revision":null,"schema_version":"1.0","source":{"body":"## Problem\n\nThe inherited pull-request matrix installs current `boa` and `rattler-build`, but its core-package step still invokes `conda mambabuild`. Current hosted environments no longer register that command, so the job exits before testing branch code.\n\nObserved on fork PR #4, run 29670113673:\n\n```text\nconda: error: argument COMMAND: invalid choice: 'mambabuild'\n```\n\n## Scope\n\n- Explicitly install `conda-build` for the legacy core `meta.yaml` recipe.\n- Replace the removed Mamba plugin invocation with `conda build`, preserving the existing recipe arguments and output directory.\n- Retain `rattler-build` for the newer recipe files already using it.\n- Rerun the hosted matrix and address any resulting fork-local compatibility failures.\n\n## Acceptance criteria\n\n- [ ] Core Conda package build no longer invokes the removed `mambabuild` command.\n- [ ] Hosted Conda setup/build completes successfully.\n- [ ] Fork PR #4 has green applicable hosted evidence before merge.\n\n## Control boundary\n\nFork-local workflow maintenance only. No upstream repository or workflow is modified.\n","closed_at":"2026-07-19T03:10:34Z","created_at":"2026-07-19T02:27:38Z","state":"CLOSED","url":"https://github.com/edithatogo/openfisca-core/issues/9"},"status":"satisfied","summary":"Verified closed fork issue #9: Repair inherited Conda build command on hosted runners","task_id":"retrospective-issue","track_id":"conda_ci_repair_20260719"}
